# Programme Officer for Latin America

{ HURIDOCS is seeking a Programme Officer for Latin America to join our diverse global team. The Programme Officer will ensure the successful delivery of information management systems and reliable advice to our organisational partners who are working on human rights investigations and documentation. We are looking for someone who is based in South or Central America, and has information management and analysis experience. 

Candidates should be passionate about human rights and have a working knowledge of current information and technology challenges facing the sector. }

## Sobre el puesto 👾

### Detalles 

* 🇲🇽 { Countries in Latin America }
* 🏢 { Remote Possible }
* 🕐 { Tiempo completo }
* 💸 { Competitive for a human rights NGO (starting salary depending on location and experience; e.g. for someone based in Mexico City or Buenos Aires the estimated monthly gross salary would be USD 2,000 + social benefits; in Quito USD 2,800 + social benefits). }

### Responsabilidades 💻

As Documentation Programme Officer at HURIDOCS you will:
-     Manage a portfolio of projects with organisations who are working on documenting and/or investigating human rights violations, which includes developing plans to integrate new processes and technologies into their work, providing training and support, translating the needs of partners into technology requirements, and taking an initial lead on defining and reviewing information structures;
-     Contribute to the strategy development process with program leadership and other staff;
-     Assess the needs of potential organisational partners; 
-     Manage project budgets;
-     Identify and develop reusable resources for the HURIDOCS community (guides, templates, demos, etc) and engage in convenings, trainings, and communications to maximise impact;
-     Build and establish strategic relationships with other NGOs and institutions; 
-     Document and report the outcome of projects for partners, funders, and HURIDOCS according to deadlines and format requirements; 
-     Develop project proposals and contribute to other fundraising, e.g. by representing HURIDOCS in public and private events;
-     Maintain an overview of past projects, coordinate regular follow up for quality assurance, MEL (monitoring, evaluation and learning) and relationship-building.

### Lo que buscamos 💡

-   Experience providing technology and/or data and/or information management support to human rights organisations;
-     Competency in at least two of the following data skills: processing, wrangling, analysis, modeling, visualisation, storytelling;
-     Experience managing projects and teams;
-     Knowledge of the cultural landscape of Latin America and the Caribbean;
-     Ease in close collaboration with the Programme Teams to share good practices, challenges, advice and solutions;
-     Active participation and significant relationships in your field of expertise;
-     An open and flexible mindset, and the ability to handle sensitive and confidential information;
-     Excellent time-management skills and the ability to work on multiple long-range projects at the same time;
-     Proactive communication, ability to work remotely and with colleagues in different time zones;
-     Good written and spoken English; fluency in Spanish 

### Beneficios ❤️

Competitive for a human rights NGO (starting salary depending on location and experience; e.g. for someone based in Mexico City or Buenos Aires the estimated monthly gross salary would be USD 2,000 + social benefits; in Quito USD 2,800 + social benefits).

HURIDOCS staff has 20 days of paid vacation, in addition to year-end office closing and local bank holidays.

## Sobre { HURIDOCS } 🚀

{ Human Rights Information and Documentation Systems, International (HURIDOCS) is deeply rooted in the human rights movement, with decades of field experience and a high level of expertise in using information and technology. We are a global group of human rights researchers, documentation experts, information security specialists and software developers out to empower defenders to act strategically on human rights information. }


## Cómo aplicar ⚡️
jobs@huridocs.org
https://www.huridocs.org

Your motivation letter and CV should be sent to jobs@huridocs.org “Programme Officer for Latin America” in the subject line by Sunday 7 June 2020 at 24:00 CET latest. If you have any specific questions about this vacancy you may contact Kristin Antin at kristin@huridocs.org.

Online interviews with the short-listed candidates will take place in mid-June 2020.

